title: Willow Tree Poultry Farm, Inc. Recalls Chicken Salad Products Due To Misbranding
summary: WASHINGTON, Jan. 18, 2017 Willow Tree Poultry Farm, Inc., an Attleboro, Mass., establishment, is recalling approximately 204 pounds of chicken salad products due to misbranding, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The consumer ready product containers are labeled...
impacted_products: 6-oz packages of Whole Foods Market “Chicken Salad” with a “Sell By” date of 1/24/2017.
